1
00:00:00,140 --> 00:00:10,720
It has been quite a week of tragedy and struggle, and I wanted to say again that if you are interested in being a part of alleviating some of that misery,

2
00:00:11,300 --> 00:00:17,660
that we will be taking and continuing our one great hour of sharing, offering continues throughout this year.

3
00:00:18,060 --> 00:00:23,560
And that money will go, and you can actually write on that if you drop a check in sometime to our office with the offering,

4
00:00:23,560 --> 00:00:25,820
to fire relief and it will go directly

5
00:00:25,820 --> 00:00:27,840
to our region and back to the churches

6
00:00:27,840 --> 00:00:29,820
that are actually doing ministry on the

7
00:00:29,820 --> 00:00:31,820
fire line. And so I know

8
00:00:31,820 --> 00:00:33,240
that our church in San Bernardino

9
00:00:33,240 --> 00:00:35,800
is currently a dispensing

10
00:00:35,800 --> 00:00:37,860
center for mercy and ministry

11
00:00:37,860 --> 00:00:39,840
in that area. So if you want to be a

12
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:41,660
part of that, you may feel free

13
00:00:41,660 --> 00:00:43,580
to be a part of One Great Hour of Sharing as it

14
00:00:43,580 --> 00:00:45,620
continues. I want to also

15
00:00:45,620 --> 00:00:47,780
report good things happened on Halloween night

16
00:00:47,780 --> 00:00:49,740
around here. It was a great night

17
00:00:49,740 --> 00:00:51,660
of ministry and all the

18
00:00:51,660 --> 00:00:55,100
kids in their costumes and a few adults in costume. That was a lot of fun.

19
00:00:55,520 --> 00:00:59,640
Thank you all for coming and providing tons of sugar that our children

20
00:00:59,640 --> 00:01:04,020
might stay up all night. Thank you very much. It was a great

21
00:01:04,020 --> 00:01:07,980
evening of welcoming some new families to be a part of our experience

22
00:01:07,980 --> 00:01:11,860
here. We look forward to that growing even next year. That's creative

23
00:01:11,860 --> 00:01:15,900
ministry that God is doing in our midst. We're excited for what he is doing.

24
00:01:16,720 --> 00:01:19,400
I'd like to shift gears and share something about memory.

25
00:01:21,020 --> 00:01:25,220
Much of who we are is rooted in our memory.

26
00:01:26,880 --> 00:01:31,560
We're a product of the people and the experiences that have shaped our lives.

27
00:01:32,750 --> 00:01:33,690
Does that make sense?

28
00:01:34,890 --> 00:01:38,750
Much of who we are is shaped by people as they poured into us,

29
00:01:39,250 --> 00:01:41,650
given us ideas and shaped our experiences.

30
00:01:41,650 --> 00:01:47,610
If you've ever spent time with somebody who is losing his or her memory,

31
00:01:49,440 --> 00:01:51,440
it's an agonizing experience, isn't it?

32
00:01:52,860 --> 00:01:53,600
It really is.

33
00:01:53,720 --> 00:01:55,810
it's kind of a death, isn't it?

34
00:01:56,090 --> 00:01:57,870
It's a death of the person that you know,

35
00:01:59,180 --> 00:02:01,040
as they cannot remember who they are.

36
00:02:01,720 --> 00:02:05,180
As Christians, we are ones who follow Jesus Christ.

37
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:08,700
Our identity is rooted in the past.

38
00:02:09,340 --> 00:02:11,980
What God has done in our lives,

39
00:02:11,980 --> 00:02:16,480
and what God has done over the centuries with his people,

40
00:02:19,440 --> 00:02:22,960
before the nation of Israel occupied the promised land,

41
00:02:23,040 --> 00:02:24,300
Moses spoke to the people,

42
00:02:24,720 --> 00:02:26,420
and he said this in Deuteronomy,

43
00:02:26,660 --> 00:02:37,150
chapter 4. But watch out. Be very careful never to forget what you have seen the Lord do for you.

44
00:02:38,410 --> 00:02:45,790
Do not let these things escape from your mind as long as you live. And be sure to pass them on

45
00:02:45,790 --> 00:02:54,360
to your children and your grandchildren. The defining event for the nation of Israel

46
00:02:54,360 --> 00:03:00,430
was the exodus out of Egypt, the miraculous crossing of the Red Sea,

47
00:03:00,890 --> 00:03:06,270
a defining moment that shaped who they were as the people of God,

48
00:03:06,490 --> 00:03:13,430
and it shaped how they perceived God, who was the great deliverer of his people.

49
00:03:17,330 --> 00:03:19,210
I had an experience a few years ago.

50
00:03:20,320 --> 00:03:24,470
One of Robin's co-teachers was a practicing Jew,

51
00:03:24,470 --> 00:03:30,910
And we had the wonderful experience of experiencing a Seder service at her home with her friends.

52
00:03:32,140 --> 00:03:46,520
To commemorate the Exodus event, the Passover, and to take the symbols that all referred to the various dimensions of the story of God's moving the people out of Egypt through the Red Sea and into the Promised Land.

53
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:55,780
It was an amazing experience of symbol and reference to this amazing event that we look back on in Scripture.

54
00:03:57,130 --> 00:03:59,610
A defining event for the Israelite people.

55
00:04:00,470 --> 00:04:09,070
The defining event that continues for us as Christians is the death and the resurrection of our Lord Jesus Christ.

56
00:04:10,220 --> 00:04:12,940
A defining moment in our faith.

57
00:04:13,910 --> 00:04:16,750
And so in celebrating the wonder in this worship series,

58
00:04:16,990 --> 00:04:21,410
as we learn more about how we are to enter into more profound worship of our Lord,

59
00:04:21,410 --> 00:04:24,690
we are called, number one, to remember.

60
00:04:26,190 --> 00:04:28,790
In our worship, we're called to remember.

61
00:04:29,070 --> 00:04:32,150
We're called to remember God's faithfulness to us

62
00:04:32,150 --> 00:04:36,450
as an encouragement to be faithful back to God.

63
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:41,880
When we forget, whether in whole or in part, what God has done for us,

64
00:04:41,880 --> 00:04:45,540
we suffer, as my colleague and friend Lowell Fairley has once said,

65
00:04:45,860 --> 00:04:48,980
we suffer a kind of spiritual amnesia.

66
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:55,660
And that spiritual amnesia leaves us woefully weakened.

67
00:04:59,300 --> 00:05:01,260
Psalm 77 gives us encouragement.

68
00:05:01,880 --> 00:05:04,840
I will remember the deeds of the Lord.

69
00:05:05,620 --> 00:05:06,040
Yes.

70
00:05:06,620 --> 00:05:10,120
I will remember your miracles of long ago.

71
00:05:10,120 --> 00:05:16,620
I will meditate on all your works and consider all of your mighty deeds.

72
00:05:18,930 --> 00:05:21,250
And there's that theme, to remember.

73
00:05:21,510 --> 00:05:25,690
Our worship is rooted in remembering what God has done.

74
00:05:26,710 --> 00:05:28,770
So first, we're called to remember.

75
00:05:29,210 --> 00:05:34,070
Second, in celebrating the wonder, we worship through symbols.

76
00:05:35,610 --> 00:05:36,630
We worship through symbols.

77
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:41,700
Symbols today, I don't know if you've noticed, are making a big comeback.

78
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:49,640
You see them everywhere, logos, trademarks, symbols that represent companies and organizations

79
00:05:49,640 --> 00:05:55,080
and musicians and tattoos of every style are symbols in our society.

80
00:05:58,350 --> 00:06:04,110
For the past 400 years or so, our Western culture has been devoted to the logical and

81
00:06:04,110 --> 00:06:10,490
the rational, and we've been somewhat adverse to spirituality, to nonverbal, to symbols.

82
00:06:12,010 --> 00:06:13,290
That's all changing.

83
00:06:13,290 --> 00:06:20,380
With the meltdown of the modern worldview, we're now embracing the mystical once again.

84
00:06:20,660 --> 00:06:26,120
We're embracing symbols that point us to larger realities that our words can capture.

85
00:06:31,350 --> 00:06:36,210
I think it's important that we have a rational defense of our faith.

86
00:06:36,610 --> 00:06:38,570
The Bible even encourages us to do so.

87
00:06:38,850 --> 00:06:44,150
But our faith, my friends, is more than just something we can logically put in a box.

88
00:06:44,150 --> 00:06:50,030
The mysteries of God are larger than merely our arguments can foretell.

89
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:57,000
God is bigger than just merely the rational understanding of our God.

90
00:06:57,700 --> 00:07:06,080
There are mysteries beyond words, and symbols can help us capture and point us to those essences even beyond words.

91
00:07:06,080 --> 00:07:17,630
I think those symbols are powerful for they help us understand the mysteries that produce wonder and awe.

92
00:07:20,610 --> 00:07:25,230
How do you communicate divine mysteries without length of words?

93
00:07:25,550 --> 00:07:28,090
How do you refer to concepts beyond our lips?

94
00:07:28,470 --> 00:07:29,650
You do it through symbols.

95
00:07:30,050 --> 00:07:37,810
And the Christian tradition has a plethora of symbols that communicate these divine realities, these divine mysteries.

96
00:07:39,340 --> 00:07:41,220
I think we've got some just to share with you.

97
00:07:41,220 --> 00:07:47,570
Any symbols up there?

98
00:07:48,050 --> 00:07:48,710
Yeah, here they come.

99
00:07:49,430 --> 00:07:50,350
You'll notice these.

100
00:07:51,420 --> 00:07:55,750
The fish, the cross, candles representing the Trinity.

101
00:07:56,450 --> 00:08:03,510
Various symbols that point to realities in our faith that are beyond just our understanding in words.

102
00:08:03,790 --> 00:08:05,930
They point to divine mysteries.

103
00:08:06,610 --> 00:08:09,870
One symbol can capture emotion.

104
00:08:10,750 --> 00:08:13,110
It can communicate theology.

105
00:08:13,110 --> 00:08:17,720
it can communicate so much in one symbol.

106
00:08:18,820 --> 00:08:21,780
Before you today are symbols that we will explore

107
00:08:22,300 --> 00:08:25,380
that communicate divine realities.

108
00:08:28,310 --> 00:08:30,270
And Jesus gave us two ordinances.

109
00:08:30,790 --> 00:08:34,370
Jesus gave us two rituals, two enactments.

110
00:08:35,230 --> 00:08:37,550
Baptism and the Lord's Supper.

111
00:08:38,550 --> 00:08:42,690
Symbols that Jesus gave us as we are to participate in

112
00:08:42,690 --> 00:08:50,660
as we follow him that help us to remember God's goodness and his work in our lives.

113
00:08:53,640 --> 00:08:58,100
And friends, when we participate in these symbols, we are experiencing something of God.

114
00:08:58,420 --> 00:08:59,160
We are learning.

115
00:08:59,500 --> 00:09:02,820
We are relearning something about the mysteries of God.

116
00:09:04,820 --> 00:09:09,000
And so it's important that we regularly keep these symbols in front of us.

117
00:09:09,280 --> 00:09:12,640
And the first symbol I want to point to is baptism.

118
00:09:13,520 --> 00:09:17,420
Last Sunday, we experienced a baptism in this service.

119
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:20,000
In the second service, we had three baptisms.

120
00:09:20,460 --> 00:09:23,880
Wonderful experience on Sunday of baptism.

121
00:09:24,620 --> 00:09:26,340
What a celebration that was.

122
00:09:26,340 --> 00:09:30,340
I saw and heard the clapping and the cheers and the excitement

123
00:09:30,340 --> 00:09:35,000
as you saw a fellow sister in Christ go through the waters of baptism.

124
00:09:35,900 --> 00:09:37,300
What a celebration that is.

125
00:09:37,580 --> 00:09:39,260
Baptism, what is it?

126
00:09:41,180 --> 00:09:42,880
Jesus said in Matthew 28,

127
00:09:44,470 --> 00:09:47,990
Go, make disciples of all the nations,

128
00:09:48,750 --> 00:09:53,230
baptizing them in the name of the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit,

129
00:09:53,230 --> 00:09:58,410
and teach these new disciples to obey all the commands I have given you.

130
00:09:58,930 --> 00:10:04,410
And be sure of this, I am with you always, even to the end of the age.

131
00:10:06,860 --> 00:10:10,980
Jesus expects that when you become a follower of Jesus Christ,

132
00:10:10,980 --> 00:10:15,460
that you will be baptized as this verse communicates to us.

133
00:10:16,120 --> 00:10:17,720
Jesus wants us to be baptized.

134
00:10:18,160 --> 00:10:20,080
Even Jesus was baptized.

135
00:10:21,380 --> 00:10:22,500
So what does it mean?

136
00:10:23,180 --> 00:10:24,780
What does that symbol point to?

137
00:10:24,880 --> 00:10:27,160
What's the referent in baptism?

138
00:10:27,540 --> 00:10:31,660
When you watch somebody lay back in the waters of baptism,

139
00:10:31,660 --> 00:10:37,140
you're seeing a reenactment of the death of Jesus and his rising again,

140
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:40,740
symbolized by them raising up out of the water.

141
00:10:42,160 --> 00:10:47,320
Jesus the Christ was actually put to death on a cross over 2,000 years ago.

142
00:10:47,720 --> 00:10:49,060
He was buried in a tomb.

143
00:10:49,360 --> 00:10:53,180
And on the third day, Sunday morning, he rose from the grave.

144
00:10:53,680 --> 00:10:55,440
It's our celebration of Easter.

145
00:10:56,140 --> 00:10:58,440
He came back from the ultimate horizon.

146
00:10:58,840 --> 00:11:01,080
He came back from the dead.

147
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:06,920
He conquered humanity's greatest fear, our own death.

148
00:11:10,510 --> 00:11:11,850
Romans 6.4 says,

149
00:11:11,850 --> 00:11:16,060
For we died and were buried with Christ by baptism.

150
00:11:16,920 --> 00:11:21,080
And just as Christ was raised from the dead by the glorious power of the Father,

151
00:11:21,460 --> 00:11:25,040
now also we may live new lives.

152
00:11:26,040 --> 00:11:27,020
Praise be to God.

153
00:11:28,900 --> 00:11:31,960
Baptism is a means of which we yield ourselves to God.

154
00:11:32,300 --> 00:11:35,440
And the fact that it's done publicly with all of us

155
00:11:35,440 --> 00:11:39,520
makes it a sign to the world that we are members of Christ's church.

156
00:11:41,300 --> 00:11:45,220
We identify with his life and his death and his resurrection.

157
00:11:47,220 --> 00:11:48,960
And I love what J. Alice Mottier says,

158
00:11:49,100 --> 00:11:55,620
Baptism points back to the work of God and forward to the life of faith.

159
00:11:56,800 --> 00:11:57,700
Captures it well.

160
00:12:00,470 --> 00:12:06,410
I think baptism is a wonderful, full-body, total-body, kinesthetic experience

161
00:12:06,410 --> 00:12:10,390
that has power as a visible symbol of your new life in Christ

162
00:12:10,390 --> 00:12:16,370
and as a means for the Holy Spirit to imprint on you the reality of your salvation.

163
00:12:17,270 --> 00:12:20,930
It's a wonderful object lesson that you participate in.

164
00:12:21,450 --> 00:12:23,870
And if you've been through it, you know what I'm saying.

165
00:12:24,110 --> 00:12:26,530
You will never forget your baptism.

166
00:12:28,200 --> 00:12:31,660
Your whole body, mind, and soul is brought into the experience,

167
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:33,500
and it's a marker in your life.

168
00:12:33,820 --> 00:12:35,740
You will never forget it.

169
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:39,640
I want to be clear about this one issue.

170
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:43,640
Baptism doesn't make you a believer in Jesus.

171
00:12:44,240 --> 00:12:49,260
Baptism is a reflection, a symbol of what has already happened in your life.

172
00:12:50,650 --> 00:12:52,190
It's kind of like a wedding ring.

173
00:12:52,870 --> 00:12:55,330
The wedding ring doesn't make the couple married.

174
00:12:55,610 --> 00:12:59,530
The wedding ring symbolizes the commitment that's already been made.

175
00:12:59,530 --> 00:13:03,910
It's a symbol to the world of what's happened in their hearts.

176
00:13:08,480 --> 00:13:12,460
Little Betsy had faithfully been attending the baptism classes,

177
00:13:12,460 --> 00:13:17,920
and she asked her mother, one, to be sure that her daughter understood the significance.

178
00:13:18,100 --> 00:13:21,570
So the mother asked, now honey, what does baptism mean?

179
00:13:21,670 --> 00:13:22,410
Are you clear?

180
00:13:24,400 --> 00:13:27,880
She said, well, it isn't the water that makes you clean, mom.

181
00:13:28,780 --> 00:13:31,500
And her mother thought, oh yes, she understands.

182
00:13:32,460 --> 00:13:34,320
And she said, it's the soap.

183
00:13:37,930 --> 00:13:40,730
Sometimes we get a little unclear of what it means.

184
00:13:41,630 --> 00:13:43,290
It is a symbol of cleansing.

185
00:13:43,670 --> 00:13:46,470
It is an experience of identifying with Christ.

186
00:13:46,470 --> 00:13:50,990
but it doesn't make you a believer, it reflects that you are a believer.

187
00:13:52,410 --> 00:13:57,230
You're already clean because of what Jesus did as you confessed your sins before God

188
00:13:57,230 --> 00:13:58,510
and accept Jesus Christ.

189
00:13:58,890 --> 00:14:03,970
The symbol points to the reality of the cleansing that has already happened in your life.

190
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:11,320
And I will say this too, baptism, my friends, is not optional.

191
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:18,340
Baptism is not something that we should just someday, if I think about it or feel about it,

192
00:14:18,340 --> 00:14:25,940
get around to it. Baptism is something that Jesus wants us to do out of obedience to him.

193
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:33,960
It's an act of obedience. It's an act that speaks volumes to the one being baptized

194
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:40,240
and to the friends and the family who participate in watching the experience. And so that is my

195
00:14:40,240 --> 00:14:45,820
challenge. If you have made a decision to follow Jesus Christ, you know him as your Lord and Savior,

196
00:14:45,820 --> 00:14:49,440
but you have not yet come to the waters of baptism,

197
00:14:49,940 --> 00:14:54,080
you need to pick up the phone and call me this week.

198
00:14:54,970 --> 00:14:56,510
Can we receive that challenge?

199
00:14:56,770 --> 00:15:00,090
It is time to say, I'm a believer,

200
00:15:00,490 --> 00:15:04,350
and I'm going to identify publicly with Jesus and his church.

201
00:15:05,610 --> 00:15:08,070
And so, friends, if you've not been baptized, you call us.

202
00:15:08,110 --> 00:15:09,050
You come see us.

203
00:15:09,630 --> 00:15:10,510
We want to do it.

204
00:15:10,530 --> 00:15:12,290
We're having a baptism again next week.

205
00:15:12,470 --> 00:15:13,370
It can be you.

206
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:15,800
So let's talk this week.

207
00:15:15,800 --> 00:15:17,920
as an act of obedience.

208
00:15:19,840 --> 00:15:21,380
And friends, it'll be a day you'll never forget.

209
00:15:21,840 --> 00:15:23,840
It'll be a spiritual marker in your life

210
00:15:23,840 --> 00:15:25,620
that you will find to be an encouragement

211
00:15:25,620 --> 00:15:28,100
and a blessing beyond words.

212
00:15:28,680 --> 00:15:29,800
You'll have to trust me,

213
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:31,640
and I'll meet you up there,

214
00:15:32,460 --> 00:15:33,120
and you'll see.

215
00:15:35,850 --> 00:15:37,990
The second celebration, the second ceremony

216
00:15:37,990 --> 00:15:39,910
that Jesus laid down for us

217
00:15:39,910 --> 00:15:40,750
was the Lord's Supper,

218
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:43,320
which we're going to be taking in a few moments.

219
00:15:44,510 --> 00:15:47,550
A meal shared first between Jesus and his disciples

220
00:15:47,550 --> 00:15:48,950
right before he died.

221
00:15:48,950 --> 00:15:51,650
In 1 Corinthians, Paul lays out the whole thing.

222
00:15:52,170 --> 00:15:54,570
For this is what the Lord himself said,

223
00:15:55,130 --> 00:15:57,790
and I pass it on to you just as I received it.

224
00:15:58,580 --> 00:16:00,220
On the night when he was betrayed,

225
00:16:00,900 --> 00:16:02,860
the Lord Jesus took a loaf of bread,

226
00:16:03,180 --> 00:16:05,520
and when he had given thanks, he broke it and said,

227
00:16:05,680 --> 00:16:08,680
This is my body, which is given for you.

228
00:16:09,540 --> 00:16:11,820
Do this in remembrance of me.

229
00:16:12,540 --> 00:16:15,320
In the same way, he took the cup of wine after supper,

230
00:16:15,320 --> 00:16:21,720
saying, this cup is the new covenant between God and you, sealed by the shedding of my blood.

231
00:16:22,650 --> 00:16:26,510
Do this in remembrance of me as often as you drink it.

232
00:16:26,750 --> 00:16:29,570
For every time you eat this bread and drink this cup,

233
00:16:29,770 --> 00:16:33,630
you are announcing the Lord's death until he comes again.

234
00:16:36,220 --> 00:16:41,040
That bread, that bread that they had that night, symbolic of the unleavened bread

235
00:16:41,040 --> 00:16:47,420
the Israelites ate on the way out of Egypt, was given a new symbolic meaning that night,

236
00:16:47,920 --> 00:16:50,980
designated now as a sacrificial body.

237
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:57,350
You see, in the Old Testament, in the religious sacrifice system,

238
00:16:57,450 --> 00:17:00,830
the animal victim of sacrifice was laid on the altar.

239
00:17:02,050 --> 00:17:07,450
And after the blood was poured out, the death of the animal was to take away the sin of the people,

240
00:17:07,450 --> 00:17:11,490
to teach them the reality and the horror of sin

241
00:17:11,490 --> 00:17:14,800
